
[1]solitariness

   SOL'ITARINESS, n. The state of being alone; forbearance of company;
   retirement, or habitual retirement. At home, in wholesome solitariness.

   2. Solitude; loneliness; destitution of company or of animated beings;
   applied to place; as the solitariness of the country or of a wood.
